      "value" : "A classical swimmer’s physique: athletic, broad-shouldered, and naturally powerful, with smooth, voluminous musculature defined by rounded anatomical forms rather than sharp striations. Prioritize continuous sculptural flow, natural proportions, a refined waist, proportionate trapezius muscles, and an elegant V-shaped silhouette. Avoid hyper-vascularity, exaggerated definition, or bodybuilding aesthetics. Render the anatomy with soft tonal transitions and sculptural volume, evoking polished Greco-Roman marble while remaining fully integrated into the source artwork’s medium, lighting, and level of abstraction. Use classical chiaroscuro to emphasize form through luminous highlights and deep, velvety shadows."
